gurmukhi: AMD lKY bDro sunY jO kwl kiRpw krwie ]2]
transliteration: Andh Lakhai Badhro Sounai Jau Kaal Kridaa Karaae||2||
translation: The blind one sees and the deaf listens, if the KAL becomes Gracious.2.

gurmukhi: khw bu`iD pRB qu`C hmwrI ]brn skY mihmw ju iqhwrI ]
transliteration: Kahaa Buddh(i) Prabh Touchchh Hamaroo|| Baran Sakai Mahimaa Ju Tihdaroo||
translation: O God! My intellect is trifling. How can it narrate Thy Praise?

gurmukhi: hm n skq kr isPq qumwrI ]Awp lyhu qum kQw suDwrI ]3]
transliteration: Ham Na Sakat Kar Sifat Toumaroo|| Aap Leh(u) Toum Kathaa Sudhdaroo||3||
translation: I cannot (have sufficient words to) praise Thee, Thou mayst Thyself improve this narration.3.

gurmukhi: khw lgY ieh kIt bKwnY ]mihmw qor quhI pRB jwnY ]
transliteration: Kahaa Lagad Ih Koot Bakhaanai|| Mahimaa Tor Tuhoo Prabh Jaanai||
translation: Upto what limit this insect can depict (Thy Praises)? Thou mayst Thyself improve Thy Greatness.

gurmukhi: ipqw jnm ijm pUq n pwvY ]khw qvn kw Byd bqwvY ]4]
transliteration: Pitaa Janam Jim Poot Na Paavai|| Kahaa Tavan Ka Bhed Bataavai||4||
translation: Just as the son cannot say anything about the birth of his father, then how can one unfold Thy mystery.4.

gurmukhi: qumrI pRBw qumY bin AweI ]Aaurn qy nhI jwq bqweI ]
transliteration: Toumroo Prabhaa Toumai Ban(i) Aaoo|| Auran Te Nahoo Jaat Bataaoo||
translation: Thy Greatness is Only Thine, it cannot be described by others.

gurmukhi: qumrI kiRpw qum hUM pRB jwno ]auc nIc ks skq bKwno ]5]
transliteration: Toumroo Kridaa Toum Hoon Prabh Jaano|| Ooch Nooch Kas Sakat Bakhaano||5||
translation: O Lord! Only Thou knowest Thy doings. Who hast the power to elucidate Thy High of Low acts? 5.

gurmukhi: sysnwg isr shs bnweI ]d√çY shMs rsnwhu suhweI ]
transliteration: Sesnaag Sir Sabas Banaaoo|| Dvai Sahans Rasnaah(u) Suhaaoo||
translation: Thou hast made one thousand hoods of Sheshanaga, which contain two thousand tongues.

gurmukhi: rtq Ab lgy nwm Apwrw ]qumro qaU n pwvq pwrw ]6]
transliteration: Ratat Ab Lage Naam Apaaraa|| Toumro Taoo Na Paavat Paaraa||6||
translation: He is reciting till now Thy Infinite Names, even then he hath not know the end of Thy Names.6.

gurmukhi: qumrI kiRAw khwN koau khY ]smJq bwq aurJ miq rhY ]
transliteration: Toumroo Kriaa Kahaan Kooo|| Samjhat Baat Urjh Mat(i) Rahai||
translation: What can one say about Thy doings? One gets puzzled while understanding it.

gurmukhi: sUCm rUp n brnw jweI ]ibrD srUpih kho bnweI ]7]
transliteration: Soochham Roop Na Barnaa Jaaoo|| Biradh Daroopah(i) Kaho Banaaoo||7||
translation: Thy subtle form is indescribable, (therefore) I speak about Thy Immanent Form.7.

gurmukhi: qumrI pRym Bgiq jb gihhO ]Cor kQw sB hI qb kihhO ]
transliteration: Toumroo Prem Bhagad(i) Jab Gadihau|| Chhodh Kathaa Sabh Hoo Tab Kahihau||
translation: When I shall observe Thy loving Devotion, I shall then describe all Thy anecdotes from the beginning.

gurmukhi: Ab mY kho su ApnI kQw ]soFI bMs aupijXw jQw ]8]
transliteration: Ab Mai Kaho Su Apnoo Kathaa|| Sodhoo Bans Oupjiyaa Jathaa||8||
translation: Now I narrate my own life-story, how the Sodhi clan came into being (in this world).8.
